sentences: Ernst Egon Napoleon Kjerrman (25 September 1920 – 13 March 2007) was a Swedish kapellmeister, actor and composer.
He was famous for hosting Allsång på Skansen in 1956–66.
He was pianist in Sveriges magasin and participated in many other radio- and TV-programs during the 1960s, 70s and 80s.
During the 1940s he moved to Chicago where he worked as a police officer and wrote music.
In 1952 he moved back to Sweden to work as conductor at Sveriges Radio.
